description : {'head': 'An assertion violation was triggered.', 'tail': 'It is possible to cause an assertion violation. Remember to validate inputs from both callers (for instance, via passed arguments) and callees (for instance, via return values).'}

swcID : SWC-107
swcTitle : Reentrancy
description : {'head': 'Read of persistent state following external call', 'tail': 'The contract account state is accessed after an external call to a user defined address. To prevent reentrancy issues, consider accessing the state only before the call, especially if the callee is untrusted. Alternatively, a reentrancy lock can be used to prevent untrusted callees from re-entering the contract in an intermediate state.'}
